event: baby born with birth weight of 3940 grams
placental surface eSwab demonstrated light pure growth of an organism

blood cultures taken from newborn were negative

maternal bloods showed elevated leucocyte count

baby remained well and discharged from NICU
contact tracing identified staff members and family at risk
vaccination with quadrivalent conjugate meningococcal vaccine provided
placenta histopathology revealed acute funisitis and chorioamnionitis
baby was supported with SIPPV with minimal pressures
baby had no additional oxygen requirement
baby was weaned from respiratory support
